{"word":"ἔξεστι","slug":"ἔξεστι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔξεστι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:imperative mood'>imperat.</a> <el>ἐξέστω</el>) (<a href='S:subjunctive mood'>subj.</a> <el>ἔξῃ</el>) (<a href='S:optative mood'>opt.</a> <el>ἐξείη</el>) (<a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>ἐξεῖναι</el>) (<a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>ἐξόν</el>) (<a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a> <el>ἐξῆν</el>) (<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ἐξέσται</el>) (<a href='S:optative mood'>opt.</a> <el>ἐξέσοιτο</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:impersonal'>impers.</a>, the only forms in use of <el>ἔξ-ειμι</el>\n<p/><i>it is allowed, it is in one's power, is possible</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic; <el>ἔξ. σοι ἀνδρὶ γενέσθαι</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:— <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>ἐξόν</el> <i>since it was possible</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/>"}]}